[node name="MechanicsOverview" type="RichTextLabel" parent="__vbox/TutorialPanel/__margin" unique_id=158082292]
unique_name_in_owner = true
visible = false
custom_minimum_size = Vector2(600, 0)
layout_mode = 2
theme_override_font_sizes/normal_font_size = 23
theme_override_font_sizes/bold_font_size = 23
theme_override_font_sizes/italics_font_size = 23
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b]Attacks and combos[/b] - press light and heavy [img=20x20]uid://dhhcof4kym2tu[/img] [i]attack button[/i]s in different order to learn combos. 
Use the [i][i]switch weapon button[/i][/i] to try different weapons. Note that you can't switch in the middle of the attack (sound clue will help you notice that) 

[b]Dodging[/b] - dodge to evade the enemy attack.

[b]Target locking[/b] and [b]Health/Stamina[/b] - see the dedicated tutorial.

[b]Destructible columns[/b] - let the enemy hit the column, or use more powerful weapon. If you are lucky enough, you will break a column while being thrown away at it by the enemy...

[b]Fighting several enemies at once[/b] - just find the way to reach additional enemies. It's a lot of fun and they could accidently hit each other as well.

[b]Chests and items[/b] - open chests to find helpful items and improve your abilities (e.g. longer dodge).

[hr color=web_gray width=90% align=l]
[img=20x20]uid://cidp1ip2hiw1f[/img] Tip: on any level you can find mechanical combat dummy. It will help you to learn how to fight, move, and dodge different attack types."
fit_content = true
scroll_active = false

[node name="AttackMechanic" type="RichTextLabel" parent="__vbox/TutorialPanel/__margin" unique_id=1701112814]
unique_name_in_owner = true
visible = false
custom_minimum_size = Vector2(500, 0)
layout_mode = 2
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b]Heavy attack[/b] - just press heavy [img=20x20]uid://dhhcof4kym2tu[/img] [i]attack button[/i].

[b]Light combo[/b] - press light [img=20x20]uid://dhhcof4kym2tu[/img] [i]attack button[/i] two times. 

[b]Full combo[/b] - make light combo and then press heavy [img=20x20]uid://dhhcof4kym2tu[/img] [i]attack button[/i]. Note that heavy attack is faster (and deadlier) if it comes at the end of the Full combo.

[b]Running attack[/b] - press [img=20x20]uid://dhhcof4kym2tu[/img] [i]attack button[/i] while sprinting.

[b]Dodge attack[/b] - press [img=20x20]uid://dhhcof4kym2tu[/img] [i]attack button[/i] right after dodging. Forward dodge results in stab almost immediately. 

[b]And more[/b] - combine light and heavy attack sequence to find new combos.

[hr color=web_gray width=90% align=l]
[img=20x20]uid://califiygvfo0n[/img] Help: If combo attack is not triggered, try to press [img=20x20]uid://dhhcof4kym2tu[/img] [i]attack button[/i] closer to the end of the current attack (less spam the clicks).

[img=20x20]uid://cidp1ip2hiw1f[/img] Tip: you can change direction in the middle of some attacks if not [img=20x20]uid://dp2m7ljkctl4[/img] target locked."
fit_content = true
scroll_active = false

[node name="TargetLockMechanic" type="RichTextLabel" parent="__vbox/TutorialPanel/__margin" unique_id=935919818]
unique_name_in_owner = true
visible = false
custom_minimum_size = Vector2(500, 0)
layout_mode = 2
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b]Target locking[/b] - find the suitable target and press [img=20x20]uid://dp2m7ljkctl4[/img] [i]target lock button[/i]. It will allow you to strafe around the target and make you hits more focused. Note that you may sprint freely while in target-lock mode.

[b]Static targets[/b] - you can practice strafing while being in target-lock mode using static targets (golden posts, for example). 

[hr color=web_gray width=90% align=l]
[img=20x20]uid://cidp1ip2hiw1f[/img] Tip: use vertical mouse movement to adjust the view. 

[img=20x20]uid://cidp1ip2hiw1f[/img] Advanced tip: you can not only sprint, but also run freely while being in target-lock mode. 
In order to do so double-tap the [i][img=20x20]uid://dp2m7ljkctl4[/img] [i]target lock button[/i][/i] while already being in [img=20x20]uid://dp2m7ljkctl4[/img] target lock mode. Double tapping again will switch you back to strafing."
fit_content = true
scroll_active = false

[node name="HealthStaminaMechanic" type="RichTextLabel" parent="__vbox/TutorialPanel/__margin" unique_id=1065952828]
unique_name_in_owner = true
visible = false
custom_minimum_size = Vector2(500, 0)
layout_mode = 2
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b]Stamina management[/b] - some moves drain stamina, while others like idle or running will help replenish it.

[b]Stamina fatigue[/b] - when stamina hits zero, you won't be able to make stamina draining moves for a little while. Stamina bar will be painted in yellow and you also will hear a sound clue if a move is not allowed.

[b]Chest items[/b] - you will find pickable items which would help you to improve health and also increase the maximum health/stamina."
fit_content = true
scroll_active = false

[node name="AdditionalMovementTips" type="RichTextLabel" parent="__vbox/TutorialPanel/__margin" unique_id=2022895254]
unique_name_in_owner = true
visible = false
custom_minimum_size = Vector2(500, 0)
layout_mode = 2
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b]Advanced dodge[/b] - press both the [img=20x20]uid://bmwjt7mmr0hy8[/img] [i]move button[/i] and [i][img=20x20]uid://covd6kks862ko[/img] [i]dodge button[/i][/i] simultaneously and then immediately release them. This will make you dodge as if you were being in a target-lock mode. Pretty handy against the projectiles. 

[b]Sprint jump[/b] - just jump while sprinting!

[b]U-turn[/b] - press the opposite [img=20x20]uid://bmwjt7mmr0hy8[/img] [i]move button[/i] while sprinting. Helps for quick retreats.

[b]Sprint start[/b] - press shift while idle and only then start moving. It looks cool but is not really helpful."
fit_content = true
scroll_active = false

[node name="UIDevToolsMenu" type="RichTextLabel" parent="__vbox/TutorialPanel/__margin" unique_id=966005287]
unique_name_in_owner = true
visible = false
custom_minimum_size = Vector2(500, 0)
layout_mode = 2
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "In Pause Menu you can find [img=20x20]uid://faceud5if8lb[/img] UI Dev Tools submenu. 
It controls all of the in-game UI panels, including this tutorial.

Also a lot of the game mechanics can be visualized using it. To name a few:
[ul]
Current state of the player or any enemy/NPC in game. 
Information about attack type, damage or speed.
Trajectory of the weapon hits.
Character hit boxes and their i-frames (like during the dodge).
Camera setup with all it's nodes.
Additional camera to show character from different sides.
[/ul]"
fit_content = true
scroll_active = false

